{"id":39147,"title":"[Functional state of the gastric antrum endocrinal cells containing serotonin in nonspecific ulcerative colitis].","abstract":"The results of investigation of endocrinal and containing serotonin cells in gastric and rectal mucosa in 48 patients in nonspecific ulcerative colitis (NUC), are presented. In accordance to histochemical and immunohistochemical investigations, quantity of endocrinal cells and those, containing serotonin, in gastric and rectal mucosa is reducing, persistence of these changes depends on NUC severity.","date":"2014-09-25","categories":"Digestive System Diseases","split":"train","url":"http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/25252544","annotations":[{"name":"Endocrine system","weight":0.810271,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Endocrine_system"},{"name":"Histology","weight":0.801843,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Histology"},{"name":"Mucous membrane","weight":0.791078,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mucous_membrane"},{"name":"Stomach","weight":0.695621,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Stomach"},{"name":"Antrum","weight":0.663444,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Antrum"},{"name":"Serotonin","weight":0.642728,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Serotonin"},{"name":"Cell (biology)","weight":0.573635,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cell_(biology)"},{"name":"Immunohistochemistry","weight":0.516127,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Immunohistochemistry"},{"name":"Ulcerative colitis","weight":0.515674,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ulcerative_colitis"},{"name":"Ulcer (dermatology)","weight":0.255123,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ulcer_(dermatology)"},{"name":"Rectum","weight":0.229836,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Rectum"},{"name":"Pyloric antrum","weight":0.113142,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Pyloric_antrum"},{"name":"Colit